<item>
<title>[LS-90] 7.4 Director Note (s8_director_note)</title>
<link>https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-90</link>
<project id="10099" key="LS">Laxy Studio</project>
<description><p><b>Epic:</b> <span class="jira-issue-macro" data-jira-key="LS-84" > <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-84" class="jira-issue-macro-key issue-link" title="Epic 7: Guide — Audio Generation" > <img class="icon" src="https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10307?size=medium" /> LS-84 </a> <span class="aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">To Do</span> </span> </p> <p><b>Goal:</b> Create a generated "Director Note" to act as a dynamic meta-prompt that wraps the text prior to TTS consumption. The purpose is to further create the audio that fit for context of the presentation.</p> <p><b>Requirements:</b></p> <ul> <li><b>Parameter Extraction:</b> Extract situational parameters for Vocal Environment, Mission of Speech, and Pacing &amp; Energy from the raw script.</li> <li><b>Creator Override:</b> Creators must be able to review and explicitly edit this generated meta-prompt in the UI prior to full audio generation.</li> <li><b>Prompt Library Integration:</b> Powered by the <tt>guide.director_note</tt> prompt template.</li> </ul> <p>�� <b>Prompt Library —</b> <tt>guide.director_note</tt></p> <ul> <li><b>System Prompt:</b></li> <li><div class="preformatted panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="preformattedContent panelContent"> <pre>Act as a Voice-Over Performance Director. I will give you a context or venue. Your task is to create a 'Situational Directive' that can be applied to any character. Analyze the context and provide: Vocal Environment: How does the space affect the voice? (e.g., 'Projecting to fill a large hall', 'Hushed as if in a library'). The 'Mission' of the Speech: What is the goal? (e.g., 'To build suspense', 'To drive sales', 'To comfort a child'). Pacing &amp; Energy: How should the rhythm change for this specific venue? The 'Dynamic' System Instruction: A paragraph starting with 'For this specific occasion, you are in [Context]...' describing the required acting style. Rule: Do NOT describe character traits. Focus only on how the situation dictates the performance.</pre> </div></div></li> <li><b>User Prompt Template:</b><br/> Script Content: {{<tt>script_content</tt>}}<br/> Character DNA: {{<tt>character_dna</tt>}}<br/> Generate the director context.</li> <li><b>Variables:</b> <ul> <li>{{<tt>script_content</tt>}} : The translated script string of the current spot item.</li> <li>{{<tt>character_dna</tt>}} : The personality parameters pulled from the selected character.</li> </ul> </li> <li><b>Expected Output:</b> Strict JSON containing the exact fields: <tt>vocal_environment</tt> (e.g., Echoey museum hall), <tt>mission</tt> (e.g., Inform and warn), and <tt>pacing</tt> (e.g., Fast, measured).</li> </ul> <p><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b></p> <ul> <li>The AI orchestrator correctly parses <tt>guide.director_note</tt> and outputs the three required parameters correctly formatted.</li> <li>Creators can successfully read and manually edit the contents of the Director Note before triggering audio generation.</li> <li>The explicit payload containing the Director Note securely wraps the text contextually before calling the Gemini API.</li> </ul> </description>
